Supplementary budget tabled in Parliament yesterday to hit Sh3 trillion.Supplementary budget has no provision for referendum. Neither has Treasury set aside cash for MCA's vehicle deal. Civil servants, the cash-strapped Kenya Airways, security agents and Kenya Railways are the biggest winners in Treasury Cabinet Secretary Ukur Yatani’s proposed expansion of the current year’s budget by Sh120 billion.
A supplementary budget tabled in Parliament yesterday will see the 2020/21 budget hit Sh3 trillion, a four percent growth over the previous financial year expenditure.



